<TITLE> USAID assistant administrator visits health projects </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 8 (bdnews24.com)  USAID assistant administrator Kent Hill Saturday visited the health projects supported by the organisation and reviewed efforts to help Sidr survivors. Dr Hill is on a three-day visit to Bangladesh. He visited the health projects outside Dhaka such as the Smiling Sun Health Clinic in Tongi, the Social Marketing Company (SMC) orsaline factory, the SMC oral re-hydration salt factory and the SMC Blue Star Pharmacy in Bhaluka in Mymensingh. The US Agency for International Development will provide US$173 million over the next five years to improve the overall health condition of Bangladeshi people, according to a USAID statement. The fund will cover maternal and child health, family planning, tuberculosis eradication and HIV/Aids mitigation under an agreement with Bangladesh government. bd
